Description: MCP server for controlling Kodi over JSON-RPC
 An MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that lets an AI assistant control a
 Kodi media player through Kodi's JSON-RPC API. Written in C on the GLib
 stack.
 .
 There is no user-facing CLI: the assistant calls the server's tools, and the
 server speaks JSON-RPC to Kodi. The only interface is MCP over stdio.
